SKILL|airtable|Airtable REST API via curl. Records CRUD, filters, upserts.
STEP|1|Create a **Personal Access Token (PAT)** at https://airtable.com/create/tokens (tokens start with `pat...`).
STEP|2|Grant these scopes (minimum):
STEP|3|**Important:** in the same token UI, add each base you want to access to the token's **Access** list. PATs are scoped per-base — a valid token on the wrong base returns `403`.
STEP|4|Store the token in `~/.hermes/.env` (or via `hermes setup`):
STEP|5|**Endpoint:** `https://api.airtable.com/v0`
STEP|6|**Auth header:** `Authorization: Bearer $AIRTABLE_API_KEY`
STEP|7|**All requests** use JSON (`Content-Type: application/json` for any POST/PATCH/PUT body).
STEP|8|**Object IDs:** bases `app...`, tables `tbl...`, records `rec...`, fields `fld...`. IDs never change; names can. Prefer IDs in automations.
STEP|9|**Rate limit:** 5 requests/sec/base. `429` → back off. Burst on a single base will be throttled.
STEP|10|Exact match: `{Email}='user@example.com'`
STEP|11|Contains: `FIND('bug', LOWER({Title}))`
STEP|12|Multiple conditions: `AND({Status}='Todo', {Priority}='High')`
STEP|13|Or: `OR({Owner}='alice', {Owner}='bob')`
STEP|14|Not empty: `NOT({Assignee}='')`
STEP|15|Date comparison: `IS_AFTER({Due}, TODAY())`
STEP|16|**Confirm auth.** `curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" https://api.airtable.com/v0/meta/bases -H "Authorization: Bearer $AIRTABLE_API_KEY"` — expect `200`.
STEP|17|**Find the base.** List bases (step above) OR ask the user for the `app...` ID directly if the token lacks `schema.bases:read`.
STEP|18|**Inspect the schema.** `GET /v0/meta/bases/$BASE_ID/tables` — cache the exact field names and primary-field name locally in the session before mutating anything.
STEP|19|**Read before you write.** For "update X where Y", `filterByFormula` first to resolve the `rec...` ID, then `PATCH /v0/$BASE_ID/$TABLE/$RECORD_ID`. Never guess record IDs.
STEP|20|**Batch writes.** Combine related creates into one 10-record POST to stay under the 5 req/sec budget.
STEP|21|**Destructive ops.** Deletions can't be undone via API. If the user says "delete all Xs", echo back the filter + record count and confirm before firing.
STEP|22|**`filterByFormula` MUST be URL-encoded.** Field names with spaces or non-ASCII also need encoding (`{My Field}` → `%7BMy%20Field%7D`). Use Python stdlib (pattern above) — never hand-escape.
STEP|23|**Empty fields are omitted from responses.** A missing `"Assignee"` key doesn't mean the field doesn't exist — it means this record's value is empty. Check the schema (step 3) before concluding a fiel
STEP|24|**PATCH vs PUT.** `PATCH` merges supplied fields into the record. `PUT` replaces the record entirely and clears any field you didn't include. Default to `PATCH`.
STEP|25|**Single-select options must exist.** Writing `"Status": "Shipping"` when `Shipping` isn't in the field's option list errors with `INVALID_MULTIPLE_CHOICE_OPTIONS` unless you pass `"typecast": true` (
STEP|26|**Per-base token scoping.** A `403` on one base while another works means the token's Access list doesn't include that base — not a scope or auth issue. Send the user to https://airtable.com/create/to
STEP|27|**Rate limits are per base, not per token.** 5 req/sec on `baseA` and 5 req/sec on `baseB` is fine; 6 req/sec on `baseA` alone will throttle. Monitor the `Retry-After` header on `429`.
STEP|28|**Always use the `terminal` tool with `curl`.** Do NOT use `web_extract` (it can't send auth headers) or `browser_navigate` (needs UI auth and is slow).
STEP|29|**`AIRTABLE_API_KEY` flows from `~/.hermes/.env` into the subprocess automatically** when this skill is loaded — no need to re-export it before each `curl` call.
STEP|30|**Escape curly braces in formulas carefully.** In a heredoc body, `{Status}` is literal. In a shell argument, `{Status}` is safe outside `{...}` brace-expansion context — but pass dynamic strings thro
STEP|31|**Pretty-print with `python3 -m json.tool`** (always present) rather than `jq` (optional). Only reach for `jq` when you need filtering/projection.
STEP|32|**Pagination is per-page, not global.** Airtable's 100-record cap is a hard limit; there is no way to bump it. Loop with `offset` until the field is absent.
STEP|33|**Read the `errors` array** on non-2xx responses — Airtable returns structured error codes like `AUTHENTICATION_REQUIRED`, `INVALID_PERMISSIONS`, `MODEL_ID_NOT_FOUND`, `INVALID_MULTIPLE_CHOICE_OPTIONS
PIT|**`filterByFormula` MUST be URL-encoded.** Field names with spaces or non-ASCII also need encoding (`{My Field}` → `%7BMy%20Field%7D`). Use Python stdlib (pattern above) — never hand-escape.
PIT|**Empty fields are omitted from responses.** A missing `"Assignee"` key doesn't mean the field doesn't exist — it means this record's value is empty. Check the schema (step 3) before concluding a fiel
